      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "APPEAL (7) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 2.25 lengths at this track in a handy 19.50. Wide box to overcome but in form and has the ability. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Looks the testing material. HARA'S PUMPKIN (4) ran the fastest on the card last time scoring by 2 lengths (19.49) at this track. This tougher but expected to be in the finish. IDEA'S GIRL (5) was prominent throughout when winning in the fastest time of the card two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished 4th and beaten 8 lengths at this track (20.11). Boasts a strong record from this draw with four wins and three minor placings from nine starts. Should be about the mark. ART OF DECEPTION (1) placed last start at big odds and is in the mix again.",
